Pulling on my heart

10
00:01:00,263 --> 00:01:03,733
Breath held, arms reaching out

11
00:01:03,733 --> 00:01:10,963
Baby this world is
different from yesterday's

12
00:01:11,203 --> 00:01:15,613
You're the only one I can see

13
00:01:15,613 --> 00:01:19,543
Baby my wish on a wing

14
00:01:19,783 --> 00:01:22,513
This sky is torn

15
00:01:22,513 --> 00:01:27,923
By a single overflowing word

16
00:01:54,153 --> 00:01:57,603
That day was BLAST's third time
on the stage in the big city.

17
00:01:57,723 --> 00:01:59,953
It was at the same venue as usual.

18
00:02:00,223 --> 00:02:02,123
They were the opening act and
played for 40 minutes.

19
00:02:08,793 --> 00:02:11,003
BLAST is really popular!

20
00:02:11,003 --> 00:02:13,963
The line was all the way to
the convenience store.

21
00:02:15,133 --> 00:02:17,343
Misato told me excitedly as
she returned from buying some juice.

22
00:02:17,343 --> 00:02:20,743
She had passed the line of people waiting
since before the concert hall opened,

23
00:02:20,743 --> 00:02:23,233
hoping to get seats close
to the front.

24
00:02:24,213 --> 00:02:26,513
That was the right decision
to come early.

25
00:02:26,783 --> 00:02:30,473
You might wanna tell
Junko and Kyosuke to hurry.

26
00:02:30,653 --> 00:02:33,223
But Jun-chan was a bit pissed off
at the concert the other day,

27
00:02:33,223 --> 00:02:34,723
being pushed around by the crowd.

28
00:02:34,723 --> 00:02:37,023
She said she would watch
from the back today.

29
00:02:37,193 --> 00:02:39,523
Don't push! I'm dying here!

30
00:02:39,693 --> 00:02:43,493
Huh? Why? That life risking feeling
is what makes it so special!

31
00:02:46,133 --> 00:02:49,363
It never gets that heated
at the concerts back home.

32
00:02:49,533 --> 00:02:52,663
I was so excited,
I almost passed out.

33
00:02:53,203 --> 00:02:55,043
Almost passed out?

34
00:02:56,543 --> 00:02:58,813
It was only their third concert,

35
00:02:58,813 --> 00:03:01,983
but they opened the hall earlier than
scheduled because of the long line up,

36
00:03:01,983 --> 00:03:04,713
and in a blink of an eye,
the place was packed.

37
00:03:05,323 --> 00:03:07,513
Awesome! Awesome! Awesome!

38
00:03:07,823 --> 00:03:10,153
Jun-chan and Kyosuke might not
be able to get in.

39
00:03:10,693 --> 00:03:12,593
What?! Tickets are sold out?!

40
00:03:12,793 --> 00:03:14,693
Wow. Incredible.

41
00:03:14,893 --> 00:03:18,063
We're all standing anyway.
Can't you squeeze in just two more?

42
00:03:18,233 --> 00:03:20,563
But we're already way
past capacity.

43
00:03:20,563 --> 00:03:23,333
I beg you. Our friends are
performing from seven.

44
00:03:23,873 --> 00:03:25,743
You're friends?
You on the guest list?

45
00:03:25,743 --> 00:03:27,343
- I dunno.
- Your names?

46
00:03:27,343 --> 00:03:28,973
Saotome and Takakura.

47
00:03:30,573 --> 00:03:32,083
That's fine. Go ahead.

48
00:03:32,083 --> 00:03:33,573
If you don't mind standing in
the hallway way up in the back.

49
00:03:34,583 --> 00:03:36,743
Hey, do you have tickets?

50
00:03:36,913 --> 00:03:37,513
No.

51
00:03:37,623 --> 00:03:39,613
Then give up.
The show is sold out.

52
00:03:39,783 --> 00:03:40,883
- What?!
- What?!

53
00:03:41,023 --> 00:03:45,753
No way! We came all the way out
to Tokyo just to come to this concert!

54
00:03:45,923 --> 00:03:48,163
See? I told you
we should've left earlier.

55
00:03:48,163 --> 00:03:50,723
It's your fault for insisting
on attending those classes!

56
00:03:50,903 --> 00:03:53,133
But the teacher said he wouldn't
let me graduate high school

57
00:03:53,133 --> 00:03:54,473
unless I attended those classes!

58
00:03:54,473 --> 00:03:56,903
Well, that's your fault for
not studying hard enough!

59
00:03:57,103 --> 00:03:59,403
I beg of you, please let us in!

60
00:03:59,643 --> 00:04:02,043
Impossible! Any more people and
we'd be facing safety issues!

61
00:04:02,043 --> 00:04:04,413
Some concert isn't worth
losing your life over!

62
00:04:04,413 --> 00:04:06,813
- It sure is!
- Like I said, it's impossible.

63
00:04:07,113 --> 00:04:09,113
Nana! Nana!

64
00:04:09,113 --> 00:04:10,343
Crying isn't gonna help.

65
00:04:10,683 --> 00:04:15,483
Listen... Let these girls go in
instead of us.

66
00:04:17,593 --> 00:04:21,053
The enthusiasm of the crowd increased
with each concert.

67
00:04:21,533 --> 00:04:22,993
I started feeling dizzy from it.

68
00:04:24,703 --> 00:04:25,723
Oh, I'm sorry.

69
00:04:26,263 --> 00:04:27,233
It's okay.

70
00:04:27,573 --> 00:04:28,663
Excuse me.

71
00:04:29,503 --> 00:04:31,663
But, thank goodness
we got in, Akiko.

72
00:04:31,803 --> 00:04:34,073
Fortunately, our expensive
plane tickets didn't go to waste.

73
00:04:34,143 --> 00:04:37,273
Say, the people of Tokyo
are surprisingly kind.

74
00:04:38,543 --> 00:04:40,033
I wish we could get down there.

75
00:04:40,143 --> 00:04:42,173
But even the stairway is packed with
people, so I guess it's impossible.

76
00:04:42,313 --> 00:04:43,413
But this is kinda nice.

77
00:04:43,413 --> 00:04:46,413
We can see better from here,
and we don't hafta risk our lives.

78
00:04:46,623 --> 00:04:48,493
Anyway, what's up with all
these people right from the beginning?

79
00:04:48,493 --> 00:04:49,683
Impressive, don't you think?

80
00:04:49,753 --> 00:04:51,353
It's because they're good.

81
00:04:51,493 --> 00:04:53,153
This makes me feel lonely,
in a strange way.

82
00:04:53,263 --> 00:04:56,283
With this popularity,
Nana may have forgotten about us.

83
00:04:56,433 --> 00:04:58,603
But she's sent me a postcard
to notify me

84
00:04:58,603 --> 00:04:59,793
every time she has
a concert coming up.

85
00:04:59,903 --> 00:05:02,633
That was a good call to hand her
that paper with your address on it.

86
00:05:02,903 --> 00:05:05,573
You know, from next time,
I say we skip school and work,

87
00:05:05,573 --> 00:05:06,733
and come to all the concerts.

88
00:05:06,873 --> 00:05:08,103
Even if we must hitchhike!

89
00:05:08,343 --> 00:05:08,443
I agree! Even if we need
to camp out!

90
00:05:08,443 --> 00:05:10,273
