SIGNATURE

255
00:13:09,623 --> 00:13:10,453
TAKUMI

256
00:13:13,193 --> 00:13:17,493
A FRIEND WILL BE STAYING WITH ME
DURING SUMMER VACATION, SO
DON'T COME BY MY PLACE, OKAY?
NANA

257
00:13:17,793 --> 00:13:22,033
This is like telling him that I can't see him
until summer vacation is over.

258
00:13:22,803 --> 00:13:23,773
Well, I guess that's fine.

259
00:13:24,173 --> 00:13:27,003
Since with him, I'm never sure whether
or not I'll ever see him again anyway.

260
00:13:28,973 --> 00:13:31,773
I ended up never seeing
Nobu again as well.

261
00:13:32,583 --> 00:13:33,943
And while he was on stage,

262
00:13:33,943 --> 00:13:36,313
I purposely tried not to
look over to him.

263
00:13:45,393 --> 00:13:46,253
Nana...

264
00:13:54,463 --> 00:13:56,063
This isn't good.
What should I do?

265
00:13:57,103 --> 00:13:59,303
I'm feeling so lonely.

266
00:14:07,483 --> 00:14:08,943
Is your friend a woman?

267
00:14:12,223 --> 00:14:13,413
Of course!

268
00:14:13,823 --> 00:14:15,183
Really? Then that's fine.

269
00:14:15,693 --> 00:14:16,553
Good night.

270
00:14:30,673 --> 00:14:31,263
Yes.

271
00:14:31,703 --> 00:14:32,573
Takumi, .,

272
00:14:34,643 --> 00:14:35,403
I wanna see you.

273
00:14:41,213 --> 00:14:43,983
Oh, Miss Hachiko,
thank you for letting me take a bath.

274
00:14:44,283 --> 00:14:46,983
I'm sorry, Misato.
I'm going out for a bit.

275
00:14:47,153 --> 00:14:50,313
Huh? At this hour?
Did something happen?

276
00:14:50,423 --> 00:14:53,893
No. It's nothing important,
but I won't be coming home tonight.

277
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:55,793
I'll be going straight to work
from there tomorrow.

278
00:14:56,163 --> 00:14:57,393
I'll leave my keys with you,

279
00:14:57,393 --> 00:14:59,623
so leave it in the mailbox
downstairs when you go out.

280
00:15:02,933 --> 00:15:05,093
Sorry to leave you alone.

281
00:15:06,803 --> 00:15:10,433
But I just couldn't make it
through the night tonight.

282
00:15:10,913 --> 00:15:14,483
Bye, Takumi. I'll come pick you up
tomorrow morning at ten.

283
00:15:14,483 --> 00:15:16,783
Don't you dare leave
your room until then.

284
00:15:16,953 --> 00:15:18,813
Yes. Thank you, Take.

285
00:15:19,083 --> 00:15:21,453
Drop by my place and bring me
a change of clothes, okay?

286
00:15:21,593 --> 00:15:22,243
Sure.

287
00:15:32,803 --> 00:15:35,033
Sorry to keep you waiting, Reira.

288
00:15:35,233 --> 00:15:36,133
Take.

289
00:15:36,203 --> 00:15:36,763
Huh?

290
00:15:36,903 --> 00:15:40,533
Get a room for me too.
I'm feeling carsick.

291
00:15:45,383 --> 00:15:47,173
The price on the meter
is getting pretty high.

292
00:15:47,983 --> 00:15:50,543
By the time I get there, it could be
as high as my wages for tomorrow.

293
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:55,553
ROOM 2015 JUST SO YOU KNOW,
IT'S NOT A SUITE.
THOSE ARE SPECIAL FOR
FIRST AND LAST STAYS ONLY.

294
00:16:03,033 --> 00:16:05,023
Which means this isn't
the last time, right?

295
00:16:06,703 --> 00:16:09,633
Nobu, you were more popular
than me tonight.

296
00:16:10,133 --> 00:16:12,903
- Thank you very much, Mr. Kawano.
- I don't understand.

297
00:16:13,273 --> 00:16:14,703
The meal was exceptional.

298
00:16:14,813 --> 00:16:16,773
How about another drink
somewhere around here?

299
00:16:17,043 --> 00:16:19,313
No thank you, I have to go
to work tomorrow.

300
00:16:19,313 --> 00:16:22,873
Right, you're working at
a law firm, right?

301
00:16:23,353 --> 00:16:25,213
What are you gonna do about that?

302
00:16:25,553 --> 00:16:28,453
I'll give it some serious thought along
with this issue about our contract.

303
00:16:28,823 --> 00:16:31,083
I see. I'm hoping for
a positive reply.

304
00:16:31,423 --> 00:16:32,363
TAXI STOP

305
00:16:32,363 --> 00:16:33,163
TAXI STOP
Yasu, I'm gonna take a taxi with
Nobu and Shin.

306
00:16:33,163 --> 00:16:36,563
Yasu, I'm gonna take a taxi with
Nobu and Shin.

307
00:16:37,433 --> 00:16:39,863
Hachiko said she's working
from the morning tomorrow,

308
00:16:39,863 --> 00:16:41,693
so I'll drop by to see her tonight.

309
00:16:41,903 --> 00:16:43,423
Yeah, that would be good.

310
00:16:43,903 --> 00:16:45,403
Send her my apologies for
not being able to make it

311
00:16:45,403 --> 00:16:46,493
to the after-party.

312
00:16:49,943 --> 00:16:54,213
Mr. Kawano is such a laid-back
type of man, don't you think?

313
00:16:54,983 --> 00:16:56,913
At this rate, it's gonna take us
one hundred years before our debut.

314
00:16:56,983 --> 00:17:00,383
Does a man like that really understand
the likes of rock and punk?

315
00:17:00,853 --> 00:17:03,083
Sure, he said that he was moved, but...

316
00:17:05,563 --> 00:17:08,423
Still, he gave us money for the cab,
so I'm sure he's a good man.

317
00:17:08,763 --> 00:17:12,253
I'm not sure if that determines
whether or not he's a good man.

318
00:17:12,803 --> 00:17:14,533
Let's split the change.

319
00:17:15,573 --> 00:17:16,593
Excuse me! Stop here!

320
00:17:20,473 --> 00:17:21,303
What is it?!

321
00:17:21,613 --> 00:17:24,573
Work? Where do you get
all that energy?

322
00:17:24,913 --> 00:17:26,383
Say hi to Hachi for me, Nobu.

323
00:17:31,353 --> 00:17:32,653
Are you planning on coming too?

324
00:17:33,023 --> 00:17:34,143
I'm not.

325
00:17:34,523 --> 00:17:37,383
I give up. There are lots
of women out there.

326
00:17:37,623 --> 00:17:38,953
And I'm pretty popular with the girls.

327
00:17:39,263 --> 00:17:41,383
At least grow your hair, Nobuo.

328
00:17:41,863 --> 00:17:43,793
I'll get no pleasure winning
her over in that department!

329
00:17:44,233 --> 00:17:45,463
Actually I don't think
it'll look good on you.

330
00:17:45,563 --> 00:17:46,463
Then don't say it!

331
00:17:50,133 --> 00:17:51,103
I'm back.

332
00:17:53,943 --> 00:17:55,273
Sorry for waking you.

333
00:17:55,673 --> 00:17:57,713
I forgot my key at
my friend's place.

334
00:17:57,713 --> 00:17:58,173
Ren's place?
I forgot my key at
my friend's place.

335
00:17:58,173 --> 00:17:58,943
Ren's place?

336
00:17:58,943 --> 00:17:59,183
Ren's place?
No, it's fine. I was still awake.

337
00:17:59,183 --> 00:18:01,013
No, it's fine. I was still awake.

338
00:18:01,183 --> 00:18:02,553
What about Hachi?
Has she gone to bed?

339
00:18:02,553 --> 00:18:03,173
Ah...

340
00:18:04,953 --> 00:18:07,283
Miss Hachiko went out
a short while ago.

341
00:18:07,383 --> 00:18:09,683
Huh? Where could she have gone
at this hour?

342
00:18:09,953 --> 00:18:13,223
I'm not sure but she suddenly left
in a flurry,

343
00:18:13,223 --> 00:18:14,883
saying she wouldn't be
returning tonight.

344
00:18:19,363 --> 00:18:22,633
I might've done something
to upset her again.

345
00:18:22,903 --> 00:18:24,993
No, it's not that.
I'm sure it's a guy.

346
00:18:25,843 --> 00:18:27,333
I'll bet she went to
see her boyfriend.

347
00:18:27,743 --> 00:18:28,603
Don't worry.

348
00:18:28,713 --> 00:18:29,193
Huh?

349
00:18:29,273 --> 00:18:30,303
Is the beer cold?

350
00:18:30,413 --> 00:18:31,003
Yes.

351
00:18:32,413 --> 00:18:35,283
So, Miss Hachiko has a boyfriend?

352
00:18:36,413 --> 00:18:37,573
Why? Does it surprise you?

353
00:18:37,853 --> 00:18:38,513
Yes!

354
00:18:38,783 --> 00:18:39,653
"Yes," she says.

355
00:18:40,583 --> 00:18:43,883
Because to me, it seemed that
Miss Hachiko thinks only of you, Nana.

356
00:18:46,323 --> 00:18:47,623
There's no way.

357
00:18:47,923 --> 00:18:50,153
But I think only of you, Nana.

358
00:18:50,233 --> 00:18:52,823
Making remarks like that as if
it were impossible hurts my feelings.

359
00:18:54,833 --> 00:18:55,823
I'm sorry.

360
00:18:58,573 --> 00:18:59,473
What's this?

361
00:18:59,803 --> 00:19:01,203
Oh, it's a microwave.

362
00:19:01,343 --> 00:19:02,973
Well, I can tell that by
looking at it, but...

363
00:19:03,113 --> 00:19:04,773
She said she got a loan to buy it.

364
00:19:05,343 --> 00:19:07,403
Apparently that was the only place
she could put it.

365
00:19:07,683 --> 00:19:10,513
If she had that kinda money,
why not get an air conditioner?

366
00:19:10,713 --> 00:19:12,243
Geez, that Hachi.

367
00:19:23,863 --> 00:19:27,733
Say, what's with this mountain
of leftovers in the fridge?

368
00:19:28,673 --> 00:19:34,703
That... Actually, Miss Hachiko figured
tonight would be a night to celebrate,

369
00:19:34,703 --> 00:19:37,613
and she had already prepared this
before I arrived here.

370
00:19:39,083 --> 00:19:40,773
Did you already make preparations
for our after-party?

371
00:19:40,843 --> 00:19:43,443
No, not yet.
Don't worry about us and go.

372
00:19:49,353 --> 00:19:50,083
I'm sorry.

373
00:19:50,353 --> 00:19:52,753
No, you couldn't help it, Nana.

374
00:19:53,463 --> 00:19:56,453
Um, so how did it go with
the record company?

375
00:20:14,843 --> 00:20:15,833
Hey, Nana...

376
00:20:17,653 --> 00:20:20,213
For instance, if we were lovers,

377
00:20:20,653 --> 00:20:24,423
would we have been able to fill
the gap between us with a hug?

378
00:20:29,963 --> 00:20:35,733
Or... does everyone endure
this loneliness?

379
00:20:56,123 --> 00:20:58,523
It's not that I wanted to
keep you all to myself, Nana.

380
00:21:00,493 --> 00:21:03,123
I just wanted to be needed by you.

381
00:21:07,603 --> 00:21:12,593
I reached into the sky

382
00:21:12,703 --> 00:21:19,113
But I couldn't reach what I wanted

383
00:21:19,313 --> 00:21:24,483
They grew smaller
and disappeared into the sky

384
00:21:24,483 --> 00:21:30,483
Like colorful balloons

385
00:21:30,653 --> 00:21:32,593
I'm alone

386
00:21:32,593 --> 00:21:36,323
My hand had no place to go

387
00:21:36,493 --> 00:21:42,963
And gently you took it

388
00:21:43,073 --> 00:21:44,133
Starless night

389
00:21:44,133 --> 00:21:48,333
I won't look back
at the shadow of my past

390
00:21:48,573 --> 00:21:54,133
I want to feel your warmth

391
00:21:54,743 --> 00:21:56,013
Tears are falling down

392
00:21:56,013 --> 00:22:00,113
Even if I'm unsure I won't let go

393
00:22:00,183 --> 00:22:06,613
Of your hand holding mine

